# pyenv
#   For a library or package, you might want to ignore these files since the Python version
#   is generally handled by the user. In other cases, you might want to check them in.
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#1255, lock files are meant to be checked in.
#   If you're versioning a library, you should probably check Pipfile.lock in.
# Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, it is generally recommended to check poetry.lock in for applications.
# poetry.lock

# pdm
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, it is generally recommended to check pdm.lock in for applications.
# pdm.lock

# PEP 582; used by e.g. github.com/pdm-project/pdm
